Today we are going to show you

00:00:06.907 --> 00:00:09.710
how to create and three different styles with only one top.

00:00:09.710 --> 00:00:11.278
I don't know about you but

00:00:11.278 --> 00:00:12.513
I absolutely love this top, 

00:00:12.513 --> 00:00:14.396
and have a lot of questions on how I can wear it. 

00:00:14.396 --> 00:00:17.417
Take a few minutes to watch one of our top designers

00:00:17.417 --> 00:00:20.287
demonstrate how to create and wear this unique multi-wrap top.

00:00:29.164 --> 00:00:30.764
Hi, I'm Kristin and this is Holly, 

00:00:30.764 --> 00:00:34.644
and today we are going to start with the cap-sleeve wrap top.

00:00:34.644 --> 00:00:38.238
So, we're gonna grab the sleeve

00:00:38.238 --> 00:00:40.707
just above where the liner ends,

00:00:40.707 --> 00:00:44.945
and the trick is fold it together.

00:00:44.945 --> 00:00:49.830
Fold it together like this, and then start your twisting.

00:00:49.830 --> 00:00:52.152
You want to twist away from the body, 

00:00:52.152 --> 00:00:58.959
you can twist two or three times, whatever works best for 
 you depending on the size of the model. 

00:00:58.959 --> 00:01:02.183
or dancer.

00:01:02.183 --> 00:01:06.633
Twist it pretty tight, and then pull it back around.

00:01:07.384 --> 00:01:09.703
Holly's going to grab it for me to hold

00:01:09.703 --> 00:01:15.108
and then you want to do the exact 
 same thing on the other side. 

00:01:15.108 --> 00:01:21.038
Grab your tie, fold it in, at the top edge of the liner,

00:01:21.038 --> 00:01:24.939
and then start twisting outward. 

00:01:25.549 --> 00:01:31.191
Twist, twist, twist. Bring it around the shoulder

00:01:31.191 --> 00:01:36.456
and then, you've got your ties hanging like this,

00:01:36.456 --> 00:01:43.280
wrap it underneath the arm, both sides, and criss-cross in front.

00:01:43.282 --> 00:01:45.440
It comes around the back like this

00:01:44.905 --> 00:01:48.900
So, So Holly's going to hold this one for me

00:01:48.902 --> 00:01:54.050
Take your end, pull it up and criss-cross the back

00:01:54.047 --> 00:01:58.680
And then you can just go ahead and wrap it around the shoulder

00:01:58.685 --> 00:02:05.250
just like this, tie a little square knot

00:02:13.750 --> 00:02:17.140
Shouldn't go anywhere, everthing's pretty tight on here

00:02:05.248 --> 00:02:13.750
pull it really tight, and then tuck the little tail up under the sleeve.

00:02:16.703 --> 00:02:21.710
and then, just repeat on the other side.

00:02:21.708 --> 00:02:28.080
Tuck your tails underneath the sleave to hide them
