00:02:28,081 --&gt; 00:02:32,22
So, there we go

00:02:33.487 --> 00:02:38.990
You might want to fix the sleeves just a little bit 
 to get them to the width that you like. 

00:02:45.370 --> 00:02:48.300
There it is, the cap-sleeve wrap!

00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:55.610
Now we are going to show you the cross front halter. 

00:02:55.609 --> 00:03:02.820
First, grab one side, straighten it out so its nice and smooth, 

00:03:02.816 --> 00:03:08.410
bring it across the body, and wrap it around the neck. 

00:03:08.407 --> 00:03:13.230
Holly's going to grab it from behind and keep it nice and tight

00:03:13.227 --> 00:03:19.400
and do the same thing with the opposite side. 

00:03:19.399 --> 00:03:27.110
Bring both ties to the back. You want to 
 make sure it's nice and tight. 

00:03:27.107 --> 00:03:31.510
Cross the back, bring it around to the front

00:03:31.512 --> 00:03:39.200
cross again, then bring it back to tie in the back

00:03:39.196 --> 00:03:45.630
There you go. So you want to open up your straps a little bit

00:03:45.626 --> 00:03:51.700
So pretty, and there you have it: the cross front halter.

00:03:55.702 --> 00:03:57.700
Now we are going to show you the one shoulder twist. 

00:03:57.704 --> 00:04:00.610
So you want to grab the opposite side

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:13.220
and the trick is to kind of clump it 
 together and then begin twisting on its own.

00:04:13.220 --> 00:04:15.320
We are going to twist about two or three times

00:04:15.322 --> 00:04:20.560
and now we are going to have Holly 
 hold it for us because it's slippery.

00:04:20.561 --> 00:04:23.600
I'm going to take the opposite side

00:04:23.597 --> 00:04:32.670
grab it and maybe give it a little twist, and what 
 you want to do is just twist them together, 

00:04:32.673 --> 00:04:35.540
keeping everything really nice and tight. 

00:04:38.745 --> 00:04:45.320
Twist, twist, twist. You can twist it down as far as you like

00:04:45.319 --> 00:04:48.290
 we are going to go about half way down your shoulder

00:04:48.288 --> 00:04:55.200
grab the ties, wrap them around to the front, cross in front

00:04:55.195 --> 00:04:58.190
and bring them back to the center back

00:04:58.191 --> 00:05:03.240
and tie your knot.

00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:10.380
There you go: the one shoulder wrap.

